  <!-- OUR STORY -->
  <div class="ourstory">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="left">
        <div class="photo one"></div>
        <div class="photo two"></div>
        <div class="photo three"></div>
      </div>
      <div class="right">
        <p>We are based out of Westport CT and Austin TX. Within the last few years, we have grown from a mid-sized regional company to the largest luxury mattress brand operating exclusively online in the United States, with 12 manufacturing partners and 35 fulfillment centers throughout the country.</p>
        <p>We did the hard work to get here, but we know our success was built on individual customer satisfaction and feedback. Our philosophy was and is simple: combine good old fashioned customer service with a modern e-commerce platform. This has kept our online business model nimble, allowing us numerous advantages over the brick and mortar shops burdened with expensive rent, excessive maintenance, utility costs and commissions. The money we save directly affects the price you pay.</p>
        <p>Today, we are so proud of our ‘ultra’ luxury memory foam bed, Loom and Leaf. This is a special memory foam bed, a masterpiece; it’s not your average block of foam. We wanted to solve common memory foam issues like excessive heat, the unappealing look and very unreasonable price. We carried over perfected principles from our successful innerspring line: the use of bio-based foams, plant based natural thistle flame retardant and luxurious organic cotton. We designed five comprehensive layers to combine the benefits of our contouring memory foam, patented medical-grade cooling gel and multi-layered quilt surface to form a truly ultra luxury experience that cools and conforms uniquely to you.</p>
        <p>Our mission is to set a new standard of transparency. Objectively measured, Loom & Leaf compares best to premium brand mattresses that sell in stores for well over $3,000, except ours is half that. We will do everything possible to ensure a positive experience for the customer, before, during and after purchase. We work hard to protect our image and we hope you realize the benefits of dealing with a company that is its own proprietary brand.</p>
        <p>I personally strive to treat everyone fairly and respectfully. My manufacturing partners all have a minimum of 25 years experience in building quality mattresses and I treat them like I treat my customers, a practice you will seldom find in the mattress business. Great relationships make for good business!</p>
        <p>I truly hope we see you as a customer soon. If you like the feel of a memory foam bed and shied away because of their reputation for extra heat, or if you are just interested in a first time experience — then you will love our luxurious Loom and Leaf!</p>
        <p>Sincerely,</p>
        <p>Ron Rudzin, CEO</p>
